# Button Component Semantic Refactoring Plan

## Proposed Changes

### 1. [src/components/ui/Button.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Button.tsx)
We will rewrite `buttonVariants` to include all requested color variants. Each color will support `Default`, `Muted`, `Readonly`, and `Outline` styles.

**Colors to Support:**
- `primary` (Theme Dynamic)
- `secondary` (Theme Dynamic)
- `destructive` (Theme Dynamic)
- `light` (Always light UI, dark text)
- `dark` (Always dark UI, light text)
- 7 Brand Colors: `green` (emerald), `blue`, `yellow` (amber), `fuchsia`, `violet`, `red`, `orange`.

**Variant Naming Convention:**
- `<color>`
- `<color>Muted`
- `<color>Readonly`
- `<color>Outline`

For example: `green`, `greenMuted`, `greenReadonly`, `greenOutline`.

### 2. [src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormLogin.tsx) & [src/components/forms/FormRegister.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormRegister.tsx)
The login and registration files use `<Button>` on the main submission and in [CardAuthSocials](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#74-113) via children rendering.
The objective states: "Nei form login register bisogna usare variante light per tema light e variante dark per tema dark, non usare le versioni colorate".

We will wrap them with `useTheme()` from `next-themes` and select the semantic variant dynamically:
`const { resolvedTheme } = useTheme();`
`const btnVariant = resolvedTheme === "dark" ? "dark" : "light";`

We will update the `<Button>` component usages in the auth forms to use this dynamic string.

### 3. Global CSS Theme Standardization
As requested, we will unify the structure of the 7 color themes (`.theme-green` -> `.green`, etc.) so that they are fully independent themes, providing exactly the same foundational parameters as `.dark` (e.g., `--card`, `--background`, `--foreground`, etc.).

**Plan:**
1. Extract the 7 raw color HSL values into `:root` as base variables (e.g., `--base-green: 110 100% 50%; --base-green-fg: 220 10% 4%;`).
2. Replace the `.theme-[color]` classes with `.green`, `.blue`, etc.
3. Make each color theme full-featured by copying the base dark layout variables into them, then mapping the `--primary` and `--ring` variables to their respective `--base-[color]`.
4. Refactor the `.ui-btn-[color]` classes in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to use the new base color variables instead of hardcoded tailwind utility classes like `bg-emerald-500`. This ensures `.ui-btn-[color]` uses the *exact* same color mapping as the active themes.

### 4. Usage Checks
We will check current occurrences of `button` and `<Button variant="...">` across the app to ensure nothing is broken. Existing `<Button variant="outline">` will map to `primaryOutline` or remain `outline` (legacy). We'll keep legacy `outline` just in case, mapping it to standard `border-input bg-background`.

### 1. The Layout Engine: [ToolsOverlay](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx#14-28) & `ToolsMain`
The true layout engine will be centered around [ToolsOverlay](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx#14-28) and a new `ToolsMain` component.
- **`ToolsMain` Architecture**: We will create `src/components/layout/tools/ToolsMain.tsx` alongside its sub-components: `ToolsMainSidebar.tsx`, `ToolsMainContent.tsx`, `ToolsPropbar.tsx`, and `ToolsFooter.tsx`.
- **Layout Grid**: 
  - `ToolsMainSidebar` (Left): Collapsible. Starts collapsed. When collapsed, width is `64px`.
  - `ToolsMainContent` (Center): Flex-growing container.
  - `ToolsPropbar` (Right): Collapsible. Starts collapsed. When collapsed, width is `64px`.
  - `ToolsFooter` (Bottom): Fixed to bottom, spanning full width across content, height `64px`.
- **[ToolsOverlay](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx#14-28)**: Update [src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx) to accept a `{children: React.ReactNode}` prop. Inside [ToolsOverlay](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx#14-28), we will mount `ToolsMain`, passing the `children` down so they are ultimately rendered inside `ToolsMainContent`.
- **Page Cleanup**: Refactor [src/app/[locale]/(public)/auth/login/page.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/%28public%29/auth/login/page.tsx) and [src/app/[locale]/(public)/auth/create/page.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/%28public%29/auth/create/page.tsx) to simply return `<FormLogin />` and `<FormRegister />` directly, removing the `<div className="layout-auth-page">` container wrapper since `ToolsMainContent` will naturally handle the page structure. (We will also need to verify that [ToolsOverlay](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx#14-28) is properly wrapping these pages at the layout level).

### 2. [Card.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Card.tsx) Refactoring
- Enhance [CardProps](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Card.tsx#7-10) to include:
  - `title?: React.ReactNode`
  - `icon?: React.ReactNode | boolean`
  - `action?: React.ReactNode`
  - `footer?: React.ReactNode`
  - `layout?: 'full' | 'auto'` (defaulting to `'auto'`).
- **Layout Modes**: 
  - `auto`: The Card sizes to its content and centers itself horizontally and vertically (ideal for Auth screens, Dialogs).
  - `full`: The Card expands to 100% width and height of its container (e.g. `ToolsMainContent`), allowing internal scrolling if needed (ideal for Lists, Detail Views).
- Modify [Card](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#29-65) to act as a layout container: if struct props (`title`, `footer`, `action`) are provided, it will automatically wrap `children` in `CardContent` and render `CardHeader` and `CardFooter` around it. If omitted, it will just render `children` for backwards compatibility with legacy manual composition.
- Update `CardHeader` layout structure:
  - Base classes: `relative flex items-center justify-center p-6`.
  - `CardTitle`: Render full-width and text-centered.
  - [CardIcon](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Card.tsx#56-59): Positioned absolutely on the left (`absolute left-6`). If `icon` is `true` or omitted while `color !== "default"`, auto-render the [CardIcon](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/Card.tsx#56-59).
  - `CardAction`: A new slot positioned absolutely on the right (`absolute right-6`) to mount action buttons (e.g., "Nuovo documento" for lists).

### 3. [CardAuth.tsx](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx) Refactoring
- Simplify [CardAuth](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#29-65) by moving its JSX structure into the [Card](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#29-65) props.
- Construct a `footer` element containing the `footerText`, `footerHref`, `footerActionText` wrapper (`ui-card-auth-note`) and the copyright (`ui-card-auth-copyright`). Pass this element to the `footer` prop of `<Card>`.
- Pass `title` directly to [Card](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#29-65) via the `title` prop.
- Ensure the `activeColor` is correctly resolved and passed to [Card](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#29-65).

