## 🚀 VISION: Standlo Canvas Engine (Mission Control)
*(Discussion Phase - Nice to Have / Long Term Architecture)*

The ultimate evolution of the POST-IT Design System is to transition from traditional routed pages (e.g., `/auth/login`, `/auth/create`) to an **Infinite Canvas (Mission Control)** experience, similar to Figma, Miro, or macOS Mission Control.

### Core Concept
Instead of rendering one `<Card>` per page, `ToolsMainContent` becomes an `overflow-hidden` infinite spatial canvas. 
- All relevant application POST-ITs (Cards) are rendered on this unified 2D plane at specific [(x, y)](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/forms/FormRegister.tsx#133-134) coordinates.
- **Micro-Interactions**: Pressing a hotkey (e.g., `s` or Spacebar) zooms out to a "Mission Control" overview of all available POST-ITs.
- **Focus Mode**: Clicking a link in the [ToolsNavigator](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/tools/ToolsNavigator.tsx#29-208) (e.g., "Accedi") transitions the camera via fluid animation (CSS Transform or Framer Motion) to zoom in and center the specific `<FormLogin />` Card.

### Feasibility
**Is it feasible? Absolutely.** 
We can implement this using Pan/Zoom transform containers (like `react-zoom-pan-pinch` or custom state `transform: scale(z) translate(x, y)`).

**Technical Considerations:**
1. **Routing:** Instead of Next.js physical routes (`/auth/login`), navigation would update URL hashes or Query params (e.g., `?focus=login`), telling the Canvas Engine where to move the camera.
2. **Performance:** Async component loading (`next/dynamic` or React `Suspense`) ensures we only render/fetch the heavy logic of a POST-IT when it enters the viewport.
3. **Complexity:** It significantly increases front-end state management (managing viewport coordinates, drag events, wheel zoom events).

### Implementation Path
If we want to build this, we should approach it in two steps:
1. **Step 1 (MUST HAVE)**: Refactor [Card](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/ui/CardAuth.tsx#29-65), `ToolsMain`, and [ToolsOverlay](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/components/layout/ToolsOverlay.tsx#14-28) as currently planned above. This standardizes the POST-IT elements so they *can* be placed on a canvas later.
2. **Step 2 (VISION)**: Replace the standard Flexbox rendering inside `ToolsMainContent` with a `CanvasViewport` component that manages 2D spatial rendering and camera panning.
